name: Zoo Society Observatory
description:
Killed two birds with one stone today. My website is coming along, and I've trapped the Earth in a black hole.

For links, I chose attributes labeled Meta. Like this:

1011001 FUN_HUB
Zoo Society Observatory
Meta:
1. Birds
2. Tags
3. NFTs
Content:
Troed tp catcj a da,med nord tpd
Tried to catch a damned bird today and nearly succeeded. The bird started jumping through the wire fence when it left off, flew out of the whole area like it was mocking me, honestly. But the bird followed me, and that's another story.

It followed me outside and made little noises like it sorta knew me at that point, so I looked for it but it flew off in another direction.

The bird must have read my mind when I attacked it to so easily escape, without flying away because I chased it over 30 feet on the ground. 

Bird jumped through a damned wire fence for the trash area, blocked from my forthwith attack. 

The entries on pages link to the same image, there's images for pages, not to mention pages for pages (those are hubs). The tags, I don't know. It's an attribute labeled "Meta" of which there can be many for users to add metatags to entries. I hope you like the idea, little birdies.

But to the birds, they must have known I was chasing them, choosing not to escape except through the wire fence, and followed me out of the place. Or the evil ass devil fucking did it.
